snippet: If Mitt Romney loses the nomination, it is likely to be because of the one region that has yet to give him a victory: the Midwest.
abstract: If Mitt Romney loses the nomination, it is likely to be because of the one region that has yet to give him a victory: the Midwest.
lead_paragraph: Saturday's victory in the Nevada caucuses gives Mitt Romney double-digit wins in three of the four major regions of the country: the Northeast (New Hampshire), the West (Nevada) and the South (Florida).

headline.main: One Test Left for Romney: The Midwest
